<h1>Problem 1851 - 2024 EGMO, P2 of 6, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 6</h2>
<p>Let \(ABC\) be a triangle with \(AC > AB\), and denote its circumcircle by \(\Omega\) and incentre by \(I\). Let its incircle meet sides \(BC\), \(CA\), \(AB\), at \(D\), \(E\), \(F\) respectively. Let \(X\) and \(Y\) be two points on minor arcs \(DF\) and \(DE\) of the incircle, respectively, such that \(\angle BXD = \angle DYC\). Let line \(XY\) meet line \(BC\) at \(K\). Let \(T\) be the point on \(\Omega\) such that \(KT\) is tangent to \(\Omega\) and \(T\) is on the same side of line \(BC\) as \(A\). Prove that lines \(TD\) and \(AI\) meet on \(\Omega\).</p>
